        "creation_date": 1362353905,
        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Displaying an image from an InputStream",
        "body": "<p>I am able to send strings from my Android mobile phone to my computer, and vice versa. However, I want to send an image from my computer and display it to the mobile phone. In my case, the computer is the server and the mobile phone is the client.<\/p>\n\n<p>This is part of my code on the server side:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>socket = serverSocket.accept();\ndataOutputStream = new DataOutputStream(socket.getOutputStream());\ncaptureScreen(\"C:\\\\Users\\\\HP\\\\Desktop\\\\capture.png\");\n\nFile f = new File(\"C:\\\\Users\\\\HP\\\\Desktop\\\\capture.png\");\nbyte [] buffer = new byte[(int)f.length()];\ndataOutputStream.write(buffer,0,buffer.length);\ndataOutputStream.flush(); \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Note that <code>captureScreen()<\/code> is a method that successfully takes a screenshot of the server and save it as a .PNG image in the above path.<\/p>\n\n<p>Now, on the client side which is the Android mobile phone, if I have an <code>ImageView<\/code> control, how to read the image sent from the computer as an <code>InputStream<\/code> and display it on the <code>ImageView<\/code>?<\/p>\n\n<p>Furthermore, did I write successfully the image to the <code>dataOutputStream<\/code>? I would be glad if any one helps me !<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 15192282,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "android",
            "sockets",
            "android-imageview"
        ],
        "score": 3,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 11565,
        "last_edit_date": 1362358674
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/iZoA9.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 2130230,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1891219,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1891219/gaborsch",
                "reputation": 15758,
                "display_name": "gaborsch"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 5,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1362356263,
            "creation_date": 1362354338,
            "body": "<p>You can call the <code>setImageBitmap(Bitmap bm)<\/code> of your ImageView.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/ImageView.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/ImageView.html<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>How you get the image data to your client: it depends on the solution you have chosen, but technically you can use the same libraries that you would use for pure Java.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can use <code>android.graphics.BitmapFactory<\/code> to create the <code>Bitmap<\/code> from your stream.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://developer.android.com/reference/android/graphics/BitmapFactory.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">http://developer.android.com/reference/android/graphics/BitmapFactory.html<\/a><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Bitmap bitmap1 = BitmapFactory.decodeStream(inputStream);\nBitmap bitmap2 = BitmapFactory.decodeFile(filename);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 15192340,
            "question_id": 15192282,
            "last_edit_date": 1362356263
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/M6UlG.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 2124019,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1886665,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1886665/overrided",
